column6: Uses the number zero “0” on personalized plates to represent both a number zero “0” or a letter “O”. Thus, if someone is issued personalized plate “70 FORD”, the personalized plate will show the number “0” like this: 70 F0RD. The letter “O” is not used. A letter “O” is shown by using the number “0”.
column11: Current, standarrd issue plates DO NOT use the letter 'O'.
